msgid "desc_task_2_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"There are a lot of resources to harvest in Agon. Lets collect some "
"archangelica, baneberry, hellbore and snakeweed from nearby bushes using our "
"sickle."

msgid "desc_task_2_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Now you should grab a wood axe and start chopping on some trees to collect "
"10 pieces of timber."

msgid "desc_task_2_stage_3"
msgstr "Next we look for rocks so we can collect some stone using our pickaxe."

msgid "desc_task_2_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"Iron is a very valuable resource used in crafting all kinds of items "
"including weapons and armor. Using your pickaxe collect 10 pieces of iron "
"from a metal node."

msgid "desc_task_2_stage_5"
msgstr ""
"Last but not least we head to the waters. Using your fishing pole collect 10 "
"fish that you can use to make some delicious food!"

msgid "desc_task_31_stage_1"
msgstr "To start your journey as a Zombie slayer kill 60 Zombies."

msgid "desc_task_31_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"You now need to kill 50 Ghoul Fleshcrafters or Ghoul Devourers to complete "
"this stage of Zombie slaying."

msgid "desc_task_31_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Lay waste to 40 Bonecrew Mutineers, Bonecrew Mariners or Bonecrew Captains "
"to move onto the next stage of Zombie slaying."

msgid "desc_task_31_stage_4"
msgstr "Next kill 30 Mummies to move onto the final stage of Zombie slaying."

msgid "desc_task_31_stage_5"
msgstr ""
"End the life of 30 Greater Mummies to complete your task of Zombie slaying "
"and reap your final rewards."

msgid "desc_task_32_stage_1"
msgstr "To start your journey as a Dragon slayer kill 20 Bone Exarchs."

msgid "desc_task_32_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Next kill 10 Dark Dragons to move onto the final stage of Dragon slaying."

msgid "desc_task_32_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"End the life of 5 Fire Dragons or Ice Dragons to complete your task of "
"Dragon slaying and reap your final rewards."

msgid "desc_task_33_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"In ancient times pharaohs were placed in tombs, locked away from the world "
"to rest with the vast treasure they accumulated during their rule. This is "
"exactly the kind of opportunity you thrive on. You know the tricks of the "
"trade, where to look, who to talk to, what kind of danger lurks at the tomb. "
"It is never, never a simple task, tombs are highly dangerous but highly "
"profitable as well if you play your cards right."

msgid "desc_task_34_stage_1"
msgstr "Kill 50 Selentine Golems."

msgid "desc_task_34_stage_2"
msgstr "Kill 40 Veilron Golems."

msgid "desc_task_34_stage_3"
msgstr "Kill 30 Neithal Golems."

msgid "desc_task_34_stage_4"
msgstr "Kill 20 Leenspar Golems."

msgid "desc_task_34_stage_5"
msgstr "Kill 10 Theyril Golems."

msgid "desc_task_38_stage_1"
msgstr "Massacre a total of 100 cute Beavers!"

msgid "desc_task_39_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"To start your journey as a Vampire slayer kill 60 Melechars, Melechar "
"Guards, or Melechar Shamans."

msgid "desc_task_39_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"You now need to kill 40 Oathbounds to complete this stage of Vampire slaying."

msgid "desc_task_39_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Lay waste to 30 Thainlich to move onto the next stage of Vampire slaying."

msgid "desc_task_39_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"Next kill 25 Oathlieges to move onto the final stage of Vampire slaying."

msgid "desc_task_39_stage_5"
msgstr ""
"End the life of 20 Thainlords to complete your task of Vampire slaying and "
"reap your final rewards."

msgid "desc_task_3_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"It is time to go searching for iron ore so you can make weapons and armor. "
"Use your pickaxe and mine 20 iron ore from metal nodes."

msgid "desc_task_3_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Continue adding to your stash of iron ore by mining 50 more from metal nodes "
"out in the world."

msgid "desc_task_3_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Give yourself a little safety net or use it to craft another set of armor, "
"and mine another 100 iron ore to complete this task."

msgid "desc_task_40_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"The tribelands are in dire need of help, you will be well compensated for "
"your efforts. Kill 300 members of the moonbeast tribe."

msgid "desc_task_40_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"You have broken their front lines, time to take on more dangerous foes. Kill "
"200 moonbeast berserkers. This mission is critical."

msgid "desc_task_40_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Next you must eliminate 100 moonbeast ravagers. Should you fail now, Red "
"Moon may soon fall. Do not give up, destiny awaits."

msgid "desc_task_40_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"Slay 5 Fenris Alphas to put an end to the assault of the moonbeasts. Should "
"you emerge victorious your rewards will be vast."

msgid "desc_task_41_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"The beastmen pose a greater threat now than ever, we must shave down their "
"numbers in a series of assaults. Kill 300 beastmen."

msgid "desc_task_41_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"A great opportunity presents itself, with their warriors slaughtered the "
"leaders are exposed. Kill 200 beastman warlords."

msgid "desc_task_41_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"We saved the deadliest for last, put them down and we can begin the final "
"phase of our assault. Kill 100 beastman devastators."

msgid "desc_task_41_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"We’ve located the source of corruption the beastmen were guarding, make "
"haste before it’s too late. Kill 5 Ironbark the Ancients."

msgid "desc_task_42_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"The forsaken dwarves are taking prisoners to sacrifice, surely toward a dark "
"end. Decimate their ranks. Kill 300 svartdvergir."

msgid "desc_task_42_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"You have freed many prisoners but the plot still remains a mystery, "
"interrogate and slay 200 svartdvergir generals."

msgid "desc_task_42_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"The svartdvergir doombringers are believed to know the nature of the ritual, "
"kill 100 of them and discover the truth."

msgid "desc_task_42_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"It is too late, they have summoned a champion of immense power. Eliminate 5 "
"Ironbeard Heavyfists."

msgid "desc_task_43_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"War is at hand, the gray orks have become a serious threat under the command "
"of a new warlord. Kill 300 gray orks."

msgid "desc_task_43_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Good work, but there is much still to be done. It is vital that you kill "
"their chieftains before they mobilize, 200 should do."

msgid "desc_task_43_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"The elite warriors of the gray orks remain a serious threat, kill 100 gray "
"ork executioners."

msgid "desc_task_43_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"We’ve isolated the warlord and his men, kill 5 Warlord Choppas to put an end "
"to this war and seize the glory you deserve."

msgid "desc_task_44_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"The malaut are scheming and have found a new champion of questionable "
"intent. Kill 300 malauts."

msgid "desc_task_44_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"With the malauts out of the way, it’s time to kill 200 greater belows, that "
"should cripple their forces."

msgid "desc_task_44_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Black knights block the way to their master, meet them with force, show no "
"mercy, and kill 100 before you return."

msgid "desc_task_44_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"Vlad Duskward is a polarizing figure, he poses a serious threat should he be "
"allowed to live. Kill 5 Vlad Duskwards"

msgid "desc_task_45_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Forces of evil within the alfar lands have banded together to enslave nearby "
"cities. You can start by killing 300 severii."

msgid "desc_task_45_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Arthains are next in line for justice, dispose of 200 of them before they "
"can weave their dark magic any further."

msgid "desc_task_45_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"100 nahdruk heretics are believed to know the location of the mastermind "
"behind the plot, end their lives and behold the truth."

msgid "desc_task_45_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"Many lives have been lost but it is not too late to protect the cities. Kill "
"5 Siharo Darkbinders."

msgid "desc_task_46_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"The giants of Cairn have united under one chieftain. Residents of Cairn live "
"in fear of domination Kill 300 ogres."

msgid "desc_task_46_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Hill giant clobberers have begun decimating city walls with their boulders, "
"kill 200 before they breach the cities."

msgid "desc_task_46_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Cairn giants are marauding the land, villages and towns alike have been "
"destroyed. Kill 100 and search for their leader."

msgid "desc_task_46_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"You have located their master, kill 5 Chieftain Khalos to return the giants "
"to a state of chaos."

msgid "desc_task_47_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Niflheim has never been about fairness, it’s about dominance and glory. Kill "
"300 winterbound or seidbound."

msgid "desc_task_47_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"200 frost jarls is enough to get yourself noticed, bring your most skilled "
"companions and take them down."

msgid "desc_task_47_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"100 ice jarls stand in your way, to defeat their champion you must first "
"dispose of them. Show them no mercy."

msgid "desc_task_47_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"Kill 5 Hjor the Great to seize the glory and abundant treasure you so "
"rightfully deserve."

msgid "desc_task_48_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Lava flows deep beneath the sand, disturbed by a sinister mind. Fight your "
"way through 300 acrids to find the culprit."

msgid "desc_task_48_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Someone is trying to destroy Rubaiyat. Slaughter 200 fire giants and search "
"through encampments for answers."

msgid "desc_task_48_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"In league with the hellfire jugggernaut, 100 firescourges stimulate the lava "
"below, destroy them before it is too late."

msgid "desc_task_48_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"Kill 5 Hellfire Juggernauts to save Rubaiyat from being entombed in volcanic "
"ash, it’s history and people lost forever."

msgid "desc_task_49_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"The time has come to challenge wildtribe ruler Grand Tikoloshe, but before "
"you get the chance you must first kill 300 wildtribes."

msgid "desc_task_49_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Grand Tikolosh relies heavily on his mages, devastate their ranks, a minimum "
"of 200 need to die."

msgid "desc_task_49_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"With the mages slain it is time to vanquish the chieftains, kill 100 before "
"you make your way to Grand Tikoloshe"

msgid "desc_task_49_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"You have overcome the wildtribe hordes, now kill 5 Grand Tikoloshes and "
"claim the wildtribe treasure."

msgid "desc_task_4_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"While stone is one of the more common resources of Agon, it is still used in "
"a lot of recipes."

msgid "desc_task_4_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Not only is stone used in a lot of recipes, there are other materials that "
"can be collected while gathering from a rock."

msgid "desc_task_4_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Finish adding to your initial stockpile by mining 100 more stone from rocks "
"you find in the world of Agon."

msgid "desc_task_50_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Rubaiyat was once a fertile land and much more civilized, but after the "
"angra river dried up, the khamset rose up from the sand to reclaim their "
"land. The bloodshed was immense, it was a slaughter. You must decide if you "
"are willing to vanquish the khamset, will you risk your own blood to restore "
"peace to the land?"

msgid "desc_task_50_stage_2"
msgstr "You have eliminated the slaves but much work is yet to be done."

msgid "desc_task_50_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"You have survived... for now. Tackle the chosen to proceed to the final "
"stage."

msgid "desc_task_50_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"Without the hands of khamset around things will be a lot easier on Rubaiyat, "
"do your best to vanquish them."

msgid "desc_task_51_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"It doesn't matter what the threat is, you've seen it all before. Yesterday "
"it was goblins, today its ghouls, tomorrow it'll be something else, and "
"you’ll be ready. Brave is only a word because most folks aren't, but they "
"know they can count on you when danger looms."

msgid "desc_task_52_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"It's not for everyone, that's for sure. Filth, waste, and vomit lie below "
"the city streets, this is the last place a noble would venture, but you are "
"no noble, you enjoy getting your hands dirty and nothing, nothing gets in "
"your way. It's a mess down there, to be sure, and it's only getting worse. "
"Scumling breed at a frightening rate, one day they'll rise up into the city "
"streets and you just can't let that happen. It's time to test yourself, "
"climb down the hatch and take them on, to put an end to them once and for "
"all."

msgid "desc_task_53_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"To fully understand doom, one must embrace it, once must become it. To hold "
"the lives of mortals in your hands and decide their fate, that is true "
"power. But before that power is yours to behold, one daunting task lies "
"ahead."

msgid "desc_task_54_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"You were never one to start trouble but always knew how to deal with it. You "
"overcame hardships that would break almost anyone. Perseverance, bravery, "
"and kindness are just a few of the qualities people respect about you. Your "
"skill in battle is renowned and you only fight when it is necessary, another "
"such time has come. Recently there has been a large number of deaths to "
"arctic bears who sought out prey in nearby towns, slaughtering countless "
"innocent civilians. It is unknown what happened to the arctic bears, it "
"could be magic, it could be a curse, but they must be stopped. With the "
"local militia in shambles, you are the only one capable of eliminating this "
"threat."

msgid "desc_task_55_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Every day someone dies from poison, sometimes it's from a snake, other times "
"it's a monster. Medicine is not cheap, the more deadly the poison, the more "
"expensive the cure, it's the harsh reality we live in. There has to be a way "
"to cure everyone, you just need to find it. It will not happen quickly, it "
"will be dangerous, you must risk your own life to save the lives of others, "
"a fair trade."

msgid "desc_task_56_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Agon has been a war torn land ever since ancient times. With so many "
"clashing personalities and interests it is understood and expected. There is "
"no shortage of opportunities to rise through the ranks of soldiers and "
"officers, one day you may be known as the Warmonger. Utilize tactics and "
"planning, learn the weaknesses of your enemies, and when the time comes, "
"show them what war really means."

msgid "desc_task_56_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Hobgoblins are well known for their brutality and respected for their "
"martial skill. As skilled as they are, you cannot afford to let them slow "
"you down. They are merely a stepping stone to all you desire."

msgid "desc_task_56_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Cousins of the hobgoblins, ravens are known to be even more skilled and "
"possess great tactical ability and leadership. It will be a tough fight, be "
"wary of their elite marksmanship and know when to back out of melee before "
"they get a bead on your defense and rip out your innards."

msgid "desc_task_56_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"Varangians are elite warriors and raiders, well known for plundering "
"villages and contesting areas rich in resources. If you manage to overcome "
"them, not only will you earn great respect among your peers but your name "
"will become legend."

msgid "desc_task_57_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Undead dwarves, the mockery of dwarvenkind, they roam far and wide leaving "
"clouds of dust in their wake as they rip through the earth and chip away at "
"the rock with tireless persistence. It is well known that they find many "
"treasures in their eternal search. It is said that even in death their greed "
"grew with each passing day, laying waste to the beauty of the land and "
"slaughtering anyone that gets in their way. If only there was someone "
"willing to take those riches off their greedy hands…"

msgid "desc_task_58_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"A true workhorse. You wake every day, get dressed, eat breakfast and begin "
"your work. Chopping away, providing the timber required to shelter your "
"friends and family, the locals, and anyone fortunate enough to receive your "
"timber in trade. Over time your muscles began to swell, people looked at you "
"differently, with respect. How far will you go to provide those in need?"

msgid "desc_task_59_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"You've always been different, always walked your own path, sometimes that "
"takes you to dark places. It started out with curiosity, you skirted around "
"the watcher wastes at the center of the world, you took a glimpse. A glimpse "
"became a step forward, and it escalated from there. Deeper and deeper you "
"trekked, acts both profane and cruel flashed across your eyes until you "
"could take no more, you had to do something, who else would? The demons that "
"dwell in the wastes are a big part of this infernal machine, and you must "
"put an end to it. Is this wise? Certainly not, but after conquering your own "
"demons, how hard can it be to conquer a few more?"

msgid "desc_task_5_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Bushes are the primary source for herbs. There are a variety of herbs found "
"in bushes and all have very different uses in crafting."

msgid "desc_task_5_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Not only are herbs used in crafting, Mandrake an herb used heavily as a "
"spell reagent."

msgid "desc_task_5_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"It never hurts to gather more herbs! Steegrass for mounts, snakeweed for "
"staff crafting, berries for pie! The list goes on."

msgid "desc_task_60_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"It is written that in ancient times eodrins were such a tremendous threat "
"that the gods bestowed power upon those who would destroy them. It was later "
"discovered that this was a ruse by the god Melek. Not only was the reward a "
"facade but many adventurers were killed and eaten by the eodrins, and not "
"always in that order.\n"
" Despite the lie, those who were successful became known as Celestial "
"Skirmishers and earned legendary renown. This quest may take a lifetime and "
"the horrors the eodrins will make you endure may prove too much, but if you "
"can steel your courage, retain your sanity, and return alive, you will be "
"known as the Celestial Skirmisher."

msgid "desc_task_61_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Sometimes the fishes bite right away, other times you need to exercise "
"patience. It's the unpredictable nature of the trade that keeps you coming "
"back for more. You remember the first time you caught a lunker like it was "
"yesterday, and since then you've reeled in quite a few more."

msgid "desc_task_62_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"The best attack is the one your opponent does not see. Through consistent "
"training, you have enhanced your techniques but practicing in safe places "
"does not prepare one for real battle, and so you decided to truly test "
"yourself. After careful contemplation, you decided the best course of action "
"would be to fight the most elusive opposition you could find, by observing "
"their fluid movements and disposing of them with precision and stealth you "
"will one day achieve the results you desire."

msgid "desc_task_62_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Seek out ghosts, study their movements, and practice your skills. Are you "
"able to move like wind and avoid every stray stone that might betray your "
"position? Prove it."

msgid "desc_task_62_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Elfshades pose an even greater threat, and thus present greater opportunity "
"for learning. Can you keep your cool in the presence of such dangerous foes?"

msgid "desc_task_62_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"Elfwraiths will be the ultimate test of your abilities. Strike from the "
"shadows and be wary of their deadly magic."

msgid "desc_task_63_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Nobody knows the smell of coal better than you. Dust. Ash. Sulfur. They say "
"your lungs are made of iron, and you don't tell them otherwise. You've found "
"a good many curios over the years, rare ores, gems, and the occasional "
"artifact. But you always wanted something more: Reputation. It’s been a long "
"road to get to this point, but you're starting to close in. Will you forge "
"your name?"

msgid "desc_task_64_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"They listened to your quest. They cautioned you against it. They begged you "
"not to go. They told you it was a suicide mission. You ignored them all. It "
"is time to begin your journey, to put your life on the line and pursue "
"greatness as few others have ever dreamed, let alone dared. Will you be "
"remembered as a fool or live to tell the tale?"

msgid "desc_task_66_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Agon is a dark, twisted place. A place full of evil creatures that show no "
"mercy or remorse. Travel to the savage places vilegaunts call home, dispose "
"of them and end the nightmare."

msgid "desc_task_67_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Carnage. There is no other word to describe it. You thrive in battle, it's "
"when you feel most alive. The adrenaline rush is an addiction you cannot "
"resist. Before you awaits a daunting test, to destroy the vermin that do "
"nothing but harm, in this act you will feel no guilt and revel in the "
"pleasure of battle."

msgid "desc_task_67_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Travel to sandy regions to hunt down sand iklits. Many bones are buried in "
"the sand, don't let your own provide them company."

msgid "desc_task_67_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Tomb iklits can be deceiving in appearance, they may look merely dangerous "
"but they are among the most ruthless predators in Agon. Do not underestimate "
"them."

msgid "desc_task_68_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Known for their signature white garbs, Alabaster Wardens are not an "
"organization and usually work alone. It is their duty to monitor the "
"activity of monsters that pose a threat to civilization and deal with them "
"accordingly. \n"
" \n"
" They tend to specialize in hunting larger monsters and are known for their "
"unmatched survival skills and knowledge of astrology. It is unknown when "
"Alabaster Wardens began their work or why they choose to work alone. It is "
"suspected that they are affiliated with each other but there has yet to be "
"any proof revealed."

msgid "desc_task_68_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Hunt down obsidian golems before they kill any more people. Though they are "
"formidable foes you must find a away."

msgid "desc_task_68_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"For your final task, dispose of sandstone golems. Though they may appear "
"similar to the golems you previously defeated, the sandstone variety are "
"even more dangerous and unpredictable."

msgid "desc_task_69_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"\"Tough decisions\" never felt tough for you, from an early age you learned "
"that sometimes it’s necessary to step on a few toes to get ahead, and that’s "
"something you never had a problem with. You're not a bad person, you just "
"get what you want and don’t care what people think about your methods. Maybe "
"that's why you’re a natural at commanding wild beasts, taming them, and "
"riding them into battle. Lately, you’ve been getting a reputation, you "
"became notorious, but you know that’s only the beginning."

msgid "desc_task_69_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Nalaeds are dangerous foes, utilize cover when needed and avoid fighting "
"multiple simultaneously, for if you fail to do so you will likely not "
"survive."

msgid "desc_task_69_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Nalaed elders are the most dangerous of their kind, just one more stepping "
"stone."

msgid "desc_task_69_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"Few engage serpentine in combat and live to tell the tale, should you be one "
"of them it will secure your reputation as someone to be feared."

msgid "desc_task_6_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Timber is a valuable resource. Use for crafting many items including "
"weapons, arrows and building modules for ships and player cities."

msgid "desc_task_6_stage_2"
msgstr "Timber is refined into wood using a saw at the workbench."

msgid "desc_task_6_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Even if you don't craft items yourself, collecting and selling timber can be "
"a very profitable trade."

msgid "desc_task_70_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Predators of the wild roam the lands claiming what meat they can, animal and "
"person alike. These creatures are feared by the common man, they dare not go "
"in places these beasts tread. But you are no common man, you stare the face "
"of death in the eyes and do not falter, but smile. For you know what it is "
"like to be the predator, killing and hunting are what do you best, nothing "
"shall stand in your path."

msgid "desc_task_70_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Time for more challenging game, seek out arctic bears to further hone your "
"skills."

msgid "desc_task_70_stage_3"
msgstr "Raptors are extremely deadly predators, do what you do best."

msgid "desc_task_70_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"It's time to take on the ultimate challenge. You must slay crogs to earn "
"your renown, all shall know the skill you possess as a hunter!"

msgid "desc_task_71_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"The Cerulean Knights are a relatively new order operating in Nagast, "
"although they send their knights all across the land if needed. They "
"exemplify valor, poise, and skill. Acceptance into the order involves "
"extensive training in hand to hand combat.The knights are highly involved in "
"searching the ancient tunnels in Nagast, their ultimate goal is to retrieve "
"the silver circlet, an artifact of immense, world-changing power from the "
"god Melek. In order to do so, they will need to acquire the finest weapons, "
"armor, and talent they can. Currently, the Cerulean Knights are 32 strong "
"and looking to expand their ranks with a few more exceptional prospects."

msgid "desc_task_71_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Continue your initiation by testing your abilities against the finely honed "
"skills of the finest varangian warriors."

msgid "desc_task_71_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"You are so close, if you complete the task of vanquishing many neithal "
"golems you will be accepted into the Cerulean Knights!"

msgid "desc_task_72_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Everyone has their role in life, some just play a more important one. Laws "
"vary from place to place, but one thing they all have in common is that they "
"only partially work. That's something that bothered you a lot growing up, "
"seeing friends wrongly punished, criminals winning in court, the list goes "
"on. Eventually, you got fed up with it all and decided that something had to "
"be done if others couldn't manage the people properly, you would… in your "
"own way. You don't consider yourself an assassin, nor do you consider "
"yourself a do-gooder, you just consider yourself necessary. There are no "
"limits to where you'll go or what you'll do, but there will be justice."

msgid "desc_task_72_stage_2"
msgstr "Travel to the home of the wildtribe goblins and deliver justice."

msgid "desc_task_72_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"The snowclan dwarves are a constant nuisance, but even in barbaric regions "
"justice must be served."

msgid "desc_task_72_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"If no one will face the minotaurs and make them pay for their evil deeds you "
"have no choice but to do it yourself."

msgid "desc_task_73_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"In the depths of the ocean water and blood intertwine. Wreckages decorate "
"the ocean floor, within their cabins await long forgotten treasure, all that "
"remains is for someone with a will strong enough to brave the depths, "
"overcome its denizens, and retrieve what is his."

msgid "desc_task_73_stage_2"
msgstr "Matayins are very dangerous in the water, tread carefully."

msgid "desc_task_73_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Before you can attempt the ultimate nautical challenge you must first "
"overcome sea serpents."

msgid "desc_task_73_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"It's time for a real challenge, krakens. Swords and magic will not do, to "
"defeat them you'll need a ship and crew. Get your cannons ready!"

msgid "desc_task_74_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Not all kings rule fairly, especially when they're monsters. Your task is "
"simple, fight your way through many knights and eventually slay the king."

msgid "desc_task_74_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Black knights are evil constructs which stand in your way, find a way to "
"dispose of them to continue your quest."

msgid "desc_task_74_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Shadow knights are elite swordsmen and possess dark magic, don't let their "
"clever tactics fool you and always have an escape plan ready."

msgid "desc_task_74_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"In order to complete the next part of your quest, you will journey to one of "
"the most dangerous areas in all of Agon, the dungeon you seek lies somewhere "
"in the Watcher Wastes, the dark region in the center of your map."

msgid "desc_task_74_stage_5"
msgstr ""
"Are your arms still intact? Good, you're going to need them. Hunt down "
"minotaur kings to earn your title and lavish rewards. They may be deadly, "
"but sometimes you must fight fire with fire."

msgid "desc_task_75_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Nature is beautiful. You adore songbirds and hum to their tune. You find "
"commonality with woodland creatures and never harm them. Peace and serenity "
"are at the forefront of your mind, which is why you struggle with the task "
"at hand. On occasion, nature is tainted, only to worsen with time as the "
"corruption spreads like a plague, despoiling all you hold dear. As much as "
"you dislike it, you have taken it upon yourself to restore the balance."

msgid "desc_task_75_stage_2"
msgstr "The next step of your quest is to eliminate oak lords."

msgid "desc_task_75_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Forest golems are very dangerous, exercise caution and find a safe way to "
"dispose of them."

msgid "desc_task_75_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"This is it, everything you've worked toward. Find and destroy baradrons to "
"restore the balance of nature."

msgid "desc_task_76_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"The Silver Stars are a group of paladins known for being charitable, caring "
"for the poor, nursing the sick, and keeping evil at bay. The organization is "
"run largely based on trust and requires recruits to gather riches from evil "
"forces to fund their acts of goodwill.\n"
" When you see a silver star above a door you know you have come to right "
"place to receive help, should your cause be deemed worthy. The Silver Stars "
"are held in high regard among the people and often receive lavish gifts from "
"the nobility."

msgid "desc_task_76_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"You have done much toward becoming a full fledged member, all that remains "
"is to oppose the Sons of Ochran, put them to rest, and retrieve enough "
"wealth to aid the cause."

msgid "desc_task_77_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"There's something satisfying about smashing things. You didn't get into this "
"business for the money, but to prove a point. You're the strongest person "
"around, the toughest, and the last one someone should disturb."

msgid "desc_task_78_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"They say combat brings out the worst in people, blood, violence, and death. "
"There are those that take it to new extremes, finding the most savage ways "
"to dispose of their enemies, with a brutality that few can understand. "
"Decapitations, flaying the flesh from fallen foes, even ripping their "
"innards out and raising them above your head as you scream in pure rage and "
"victorious bliss."

msgid "desc_task_78_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Stoneguards are even more dangerous than what you've encountered thus far, "
"be ready for anything and prepared for the worst."

msgid "desc_task_78_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Menhir sentinels are the perfect opponents to test your skills and put on a "
"brutal display that all shall remember."

msgid "desc_task_79_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Under the blanket of night nocturnal creatures emerge to feast upon "
"unsuspecting prey. You must wait until the sun subsides, draw them out, and "
"slay them. Only then will you be rewarded with a suitably dark gift."

msgid "desc_task_79_stage_2"
msgstr "Night hags are devious creatures full of hatred, show them no mercy."

msgid "desc_task_79_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Thainlords are finely trained and utilize tactics passed down over "
"generations. If you can dispose of them you will have earned the title of "
"Night Stalker."

msgid "desc_task_7_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Fish is an excellent source of food. Using pots and pans at an oven will "
"yield some tasy treats. Combine fish with other harvested items for even "
"tastier treats!"

msgid "desc_task_7_stage_2"
msgstr "Use your fishing pole to reel in 50 more fish from the waters."

msgid "desc_task_7_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"As you gather more fish you'll notice a lot of other resources can be "
"collected while on the water."

msgid "desc_task_80_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Animals love to eat steedgrass. It’s not easy to find but with patience, you "
"always manage. Seeing and hearing the pleasure of animals eating their "
"favorite snack is a wonderful experience, of which you aim to enjoy as often "
"as possible."

msgid "desc_task_81_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Like the roots of an old tree, the history of Agon is vast. The remnants of "
"ancient civilizations and battles long forgotten still lie beneath the "
"ground we walk on, awaiting discovery..."

msgid "desc_task_81_stage_2"
msgstr "Lots of goodies get swept ashore, making beaches an ideal spot to dig."

msgid "desc_task_81_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Cairn is the only place you'll find clay. Be careful though, you may find "
"the inhabitants are not so friendly..."

msgid "desc_task_82_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Picking berries is a lot of fun, and watching your basket slowly fill up is "
"awesome. Why spend your hard earned gold on something you can acquire "
"yourself for free?"

msgid "desc_task_83_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Herbs are wonderful things. Whether someone is sick, depressed, or nervous, "
"it can all go away with the right concoction. You provide what people need "
"and whether they like your prices or not, they depend on you to take care of "
"them."

msgid "desc_task_84_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Mahogany seems to only grow in the most dangerous places, but that never "
"deterred you. They say what’s worth having is worth fighting for, you always "
"found that to be true. It’s not only due to the fact that mahogany is a "
"precious commodity, but also because you find solace in the woods."

msgid "desc_task_85_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Lobsters are a favorite food all over Agon, and lobstermen tend to do well "
"for themselves financially. Whether it’s your occupation or hobby, it "
"requires great waterman aptitude and diligence."

msgid "desc_task_86_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"In the old days, this was merely a hobby. You started out by collecting "
"shiny stones and building your collection, but once you realized the value "
"of limestone it became a quick and obvious transition. One of the most "
"satisfying aspects is that your efforts help others build their homes, "
"making the whole experience more rewarding than just profit, but profit "
"never hurts."

msgid "desc_task_87_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Pies, tarts, cakes… the joy of eating desserts is pure bliss. Whether you’re "
"baking for yourself or providing a savory treat for your friends, you take "
"care to acquire the highest quality ingredients."

msgid "desc_task_88_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Your upbringing was a mixture of blessings and curses, leading you to live a "
"chaotic but exciting life. You have managed to earn the respect of the "
"masses and your name is of great repute, but soon it may become legendary."

msgid "desc_task_88_stage_2"
msgstr "Seek out and destroy the gravelords, their evil must come to an end!"

msgid "desc_task_88_stage_3"
msgstr "Defeat the men of your greatest enemy, but beware of their depravity."

msgid "desc_task_88_stage_4"
msgstr "Overcome seemingly impossible odds by felling the giant!"

msgid "desc_task_89_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Life is full of surprises, sometimes it feels like a game, other times you "
"feel trapped and seek to escape. Throughout it all, you have found that "
"swordsmanship is your true calling, and there is no one out there that can "
"match your degree of mastery. Each successful attack with greatswords will "
"yield progress."

msgid "desc_task_8_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"It looks like you've discovered some kobolds! They are pesky little buggers, "
"so try and thin out some of their ranks ! Kill any 10 kobolds to receive "
"your reward."

msgid "desc_task_8_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Just like rats, more kobolds have appeared, only meaning it is time to kill "
"some more! Kill 50 more kobolds to receive your reward."

msgid "desc_task_8_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Lay waste to the kobold masses and take a stand against their kin! Kill 150 "
"more kobolds to receive your reward."

msgid "desc_task_90_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Stay awhile and listen. There have been rumors of a secret place full of "
"loot and utter insanity. Though you have no beef with the inhabitants, you "
"have decided to milk it for all it’s worth. In the end, you do whatever "
"behooves you."

msgid "desc_task_91_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"You are known for your beauty and grace, many think you would not harm a "
"fly. Many are wrong. Battle may not be pretty but it is what makes you feel "
"alive, there is no greater rush than fighting for a cause you believe in and "
"living to tell the tale."

msgid "desc_task_92_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"You are mocked for your small stature and doubted by many, but that has "
"never stopped you from getting what you want. In fact, you relish the "
"challenge and when it’s all said and done it is usually you that does the "
"mocking. Each successful attack with cursed bolt will yield progress."

msgid "desc_task_93_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"You have a fiery temper and a reputation for being destructive. Diplomacy "
"and reason are not your strong suits, instead, you prefer to lay waste to "
"anyone or anything that gets in your way."

msgid "desc_task_93_stage_2"
msgstr "Heed the challenge of the lava golems!"

msgid "desc_task_93_stage_3"
msgstr "Firescourges are next, can you prove your combat prowess?"

msgid "desc_task_93_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"Survive against erodachs, see what you can learn, and return home with even "
"greater power."

msgid "desc_task_93_stage_5"
msgstr ""
"The game has just become much deadlier. Battle the fire dragon, only then "
"will you gain true mastery of the flame."

msgid "desc_task_94_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Your life is full of danger and excitement. Plundering trade ships and "
"raiding coastal cities are some of your favorite hobbies, you also enjoy "
"counting your gold. After losing your ship in a particularly nasty battle "
"you decided to do a few favors in return for materials to build a new ship, "
"and the first favor involves brownie hunting, what comes next is anyone's "
"guess."

msgid "desc_task_94_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"It didn't take much to convince you to teach a lesson to some of your most "
"hated enemies, the bonecrew are all that stands between you and a huge pile "
"of ship building materials."

msgid "desc_task_94_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Your next quest gave you some pause, seaserpents are quite dangerous, but "
"they're nothing compared to your crew, so if you can deal with them this "
"should be no challenge."

msgid "desc_task_94_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"It's time to face the ultimate monstrosity of the open seas. Time to get "
"your crew together and see what you're made of!"

msgid "desc_task_95_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"There are those that doubt your methods but you are generally well received. "
"It is true that in order to achieve the greatest victories, sacrifices must "
"be made. Such means are not for the faint of heart, they are precisely for "
"those with great inner courage. Each successful attack with firebolt will "
"yield progress."

msgid "desc_task_96_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Ah the nahdruk, they think so highly of themselves. Powerful in martial "
"combat, impressive magic, well organized tactics… the perfect targets to "
"hone your skills on. It won’t be easy, it won’t be safe, but it will be "
"glorious. If you can assassinate the nahdruk, you can assassinate just about "
"anyone. No time like the present. Each successful attack with knives will "
"yield progress."

msgid "desc_task_97_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Life on the run is difficult, especially with no place to call home and few "
"people you can trust. You get by simply through criminal means and over time "
"you felt less and less remorse for the lives you have taken."

msgid "desc_task_97_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"The life of a mercenary is never easy. You will be paid handsomely for "
"fighting the Forest Prophets."

msgid "desc_task_97_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"You have discovered an enticing bounty for killing Ork outcasts, collect it "
"before someone else does."

msgid "desc_task_97_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"Svartdvergirs are up to no good, but what else is new? Hunt them down to "
"collect the bounty and fill your belly."

msgid "desc_task_97_stage_5"
msgstr ""
"Opportunities are always available for those willing to get their hands "
"dirty, those Moonbeasts don't deserve to live anyway."

msgid "desc_task_97_stage_6"
msgstr ""
"Another bounty is available, this time for killing Melechars. Watch your "
"back, they are known to be treacherous foes."

msgid "desc_task_98_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Though you have been doubted many times you always emerge victoriously and "
"prove those who question you to be fools. You are one of the very rare "
"individuals capable of associating with dragons, a quality which has proven "
"to be a tremendous boon in your pursuits. Though you have accomplished much, "
"there is much to be done before you achieve your greatest dreams."

msgid "desc_task_98_stage_2"
msgstr "Show the Sun Exarchs that they are no match for you."

msgid "desc_task_98_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Dark Dragons are menacing indeed but surely they will not stand in your way."

msgid "desc_task_98_stage_4"
msgstr ""
"Travel to the place Gardorocs reside and make them bow before your greatness."

msgid "desc_task_98_stage_5"
msgstr "Show the fire dragon that no flame is intense enough to burn you."

msgid "desc_task_98_stage_6"
msgstr ""
"It has been a long journey but it is time to fight Kroshogo the Ice Dragon "
"and claim all that is yours!"

msgid "desc_task_99_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"You are well known for your incredible physique and massive stature, but "
"also for your penchant for brutality. You have overcome many epic "
"challenges, but there are more yet to come."

msgid "desc_task_99_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"Few are capable of overpowering the Chosen of Khamset, but they should be no "
"challenge for you."

msgid "desc_task_99_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Icejarls are some of the meanest and most powerful beings in the land. Are "
"you mighty enough to topple them?"

msgid "desc_task_99_stage_4"
msgstr "Cairn giants will be daunting foes...annihilate them."

msgid "desc_task_99_stage_5"
msgstr ""
"Your final test will be to go toe to toe with fire giants, can you overcome "
"their wrath?"

msgid "desc_task_9_stage_1"
msgstr ""
"Now that you have killed your first troll, it's time to kill a few more! "
"Kill any 10 trolls to receive your reward."

msgid "desc_task_9_stage_2"
msgstr ""
"The trolls were undeterred by your most recent attack! Kill 50 more trolls "
"to receive your reward."

msgid "desc_task_9_stage_3"
msgstr ""
"Take the fight to the trolls and lay waste to their kin! Kill 150 more "
"trolls to receive your reward."

